  <div class="col p-4 d-flex flex-column position-static">
    <h3><button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm d-lg-none">Step Five</button> Attend a Trial Day</h3>
    <p class="card-text mb-auto">We don't use entrance exams but we do like to meet the student, get to know them and see if they would be happy in our school.</p>

    <div class="text-muted mt-3">In Japan</div>
    <p class="card-text mb-auto">The trial for students aged 2 - 5 years old is from 9.00am to 1.00pm. For students aged 6  and over it is 8.30am to 3.30pm. Teachers will observe the student and assess their language skills, academic level and general aptitude.<br>
    Following the trial day, an interview will take place or the school office will telephone you to notify about the child’s trial result.</p>

    <div class="text-muted mt-3">Outside Japan</div>
    <p class="card-text mb-auto">We understand that not all families are able to have the child attend for a trial day in advance of enrolment. In the case of overseas families, we will pass this step, and make admissions decisions based on the report cards and confidential reference.</p>
  </div>
</div>

